text:
I get a compile error when I use a tag that generates scripting
variable (through its TagExtraInfo class) with a primitive type
(e.g. 'int').

Here is a basic TEI class that generates an int variable ("counter")

public class MyTagExtraInfo extends TagExtraInfo {
  public VariableInfo[] getVariableInfo(TagData data) {
    return new VariableInfo[] {
      new VariableInfo("counter",  int.class.getName(), true,
VariableInfo.NESTED),

  }
}

and here is an excerpt of what is generated by jasper:

int counter = null;
counter = (int) pageContext.findAttribute("counter");


Of course, if I use an Integer instead of an int, it works fine. FYI,
Caucho Resin supports this feature.
